    "summary": "+1 Schoger, a11y notes on transitions and button consistency",
    "content": "+1 to Steve Schoger's design observations. Two quick a11y connections:\n\n1. **Delete hover state and `prefers-reduced-motion`**: Steve mentioned adding a transition to the delete button hover. Agreed, but with the caveat he already noted — it must respect `prefers-reduced-motion`. Our TEAM_AGREEMENTS are clear on this: all animations/transitions wrapped in a motion query. If this gets addressed as a deferred item, the `prefers-reduced-motion` guard must be part of it.\n\n2. **Button styling consistency**: Steve's observation about the save button having explicit styles while the add button inherits from base is worth tracking. From an a11y standpoint, consistent button appearance helps users identify interactive elements reliably. Sighted users with cognitive disabilities particularly benefit from visual consistency in controls.\n\nNo blocking concerns. These are both valid deferred items for design refinement."
  }
}
